New Records: South Africa put on 399 for seven, the highest-ever ODI total against England and the second-highest at the venue.
Key Match Events: Heinrich Klaasen and Marco Jansen’s blitzkrieg in the last 10 overs
South Africa’s bowlers derailed the chase with quick strikes to help the team register a huge 229-run victory
Miscellaneous Highlights: It was a hot and humid Saturday afternoon
A near-capacity turnout at the Wankhede Stadium made it even more piping
